Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Chop the @sweet potatoes{2} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop the potatoes on a low-sided, wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out in a single layer. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Meanwhile, chop the @smoked tofu{225%g} into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with some #kitchen paper{}. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the tofu to the pan, fry until golden all over, ~{6-8%minutes}, turning occasionally. Tip the tofu into a #bowl{} and set aside. Keep the pan.

While the tofu cooks, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Thinly slice half the @red chilli{1/2}(thinly sliced) and finely chop the rest. Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}(zested and halved).

Pop the pan back on a medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. Once hot, add the shallot to the pan and fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the garlic, @ginger puree{1%tsp}, finely chopped chilli (careful it's hot - add less if you don't like heat) and @tomato puree{30%g}. Cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @water{200%ml} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}.

Bring to the boil and simmer until the sauce has reduced slightly, stirring occasionally, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the @baby spinach{40%g} a handful at a time until it's wilted and everything is piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat, squeeze in some of the lime juice and add half the @soy sauce{25%ml}. Taste and add more lime juice and soy sauce if you feel it needs it, then stir in the roasted sweet potato and tofu.

> TIP: Add a splash more water to the stew if it's a bit dry.

Serve in #bowls{} with the sliced chilli (careful it's hot - add less if you don't like heat) and lime zest sprinkled on top. Enjoy!